<item>
            <title>[LU-6535] updating fsname and index wth different orders have problems</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6535</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Updating fsname with following command failed:&lt;br/&gt;
tunefs.lustre --fsname lustre --writeconf /dev/mgs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But using following command succeed:&lt;br/&gt;
tunefs.lustre --writeconf --fsname lustre /dev/mgs&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IT turned out this is because of options parsing order,&lt;br/&gt;
but actually, we should let both two ways work, so fix is also simple to&lt;br/&gt;
do sanity check after we have parsed all options. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
